The paper analyzes citation relations among journals, which falls under the field of bibliometrics and scientometrics. The use of power-laws and self-organized criticality suggests a quantitative approach, which is commonly found in the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries). The analysis of citation relations also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the mention of "change" and "innovation" suggests a potential connection to software development (cs.SD).
